Objective: Deploying applications to free cloud hosting providers (Heroku, Netlify, etc.), Rollback strategies, 
Monitoring deployments. 
Required Software / Tools: VSCode, HTML, Nelify/Heroku cloud. 
Procedure: 
1. Set up a Working directory or folder as below: 
Open Visual Studio > Menu options > File > Open Folder > Right click > create New Folder with name Exp7. 
2. Open terminal from visual studio > Menu options > Terminal > New Terminal. 
3. Create a new file with below code and save it as index.html. 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
<title>Student Web Application</title> 
</head> 
<body> 
<h1>Welcome to My Website</h1> 
<p> 
This website is deployed using Netlify cloud hosting platform. 
</p> 
<a href="about.html">About Page</a> 
</body> 
</html> 
4. Now create one more file with below code and save it as about.html. 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html> 
<head> 
<title>About Page</title> 
</head> 
<body> 
<h1>About This Project</h1> 
<p> 
This is a simple static website hosted on Netlify. 
</p> 
<p> 
Netlify provides free cloud hosting for frontend applications and static websites. 
</p> 
<a href="index.html">Back to Home</a> 
</body> 
</html> 
5. Verify from local > navigate to Exp7 folder and double click index.html. 
6. Signup for Nelify using google account.  
https://app.netlify.com/signup 
7. Click continue to deploy. Now you should be able to see Deploy project page. 
8. Now, drag and drop Exp7 folder to Nelify. 
9. Click on the url generated to validate the cloud deployment. 
10. You can configure project by navigating to quick setup. 
11. You can monitor using observability. 
